  "texts": [
    "Punctuation errors indicated to participants that the text had been generated by a human.",
    "Structure in general was reported as a criterion, but with disagreement between participants: some considered texts to be AI-generated when they were well-structured, while others considered such texts to be human-generated.",
    "Tone was also considered as a factor influencing the choice of some participants, with a conversational tone considered more likely to be human-generated.",
    "Readability was also highlighted: if a text was difficult to read, it was thought to be AI-generated.",
    "• Vocabulary (32/42)."
